{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"code":["ðŸ§¬ Theme version: 1.5.0"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some Orange products can be designed for very specific use cases. For example dark environments, or for users always on screen or for mobility uses cases.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Thus this inverse theme is based on the Orange theme and it tailored with a dedicated color palette.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This theme is related to Orange theme module to use some raw tokens of colors."}]}]},{"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Orange Inverse theme does not embed charts colors yet, and is read-only: it cannot be suclassed or derivated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":2,"text":"How to use the theme","anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeInverse\/OrangeInverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. To use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeInverse\/OrangeInverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" without further modifications, you will have to use the "},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for your root view and give it an instance of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeInverse\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeInverse\/OrangeInverseTheme"},{"type":"text","text":". Keep in mind the themes are "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift class objects","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"tex